FBIS4-63095 "drsov098_p_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 18 May 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia Press Secretary Hopes Azerbaijan To Show `Common Sense' Press Secretary Hopes Azerbaijan To Show `Common Sense' NC1905064294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1454 GMT 18 May 94 NC1905064294 Yerevan SNARK English BFN [Text] Yerevan, 18 May (SNARK)--Levon Zurabyan, acting press-secretary of the Armenian president, declared today that the sides of the Karabakh conflict have never been so close to peace as they are now. "The road to the armistice is difficult, but the negotiations are going on and Armenia hopes that the Azerbaijani leadership will display common sense and sign the agreement," said Mr. Zurabyan at a briefing in Yerevan. He also declared that Armenia welcomes and highly estimates the readiness of Russia "to undertake the burden of peace-keeping forces' deployment in the region."
